The paper presents a novel approach for training a Variational Autoencoder (VAE) on a highly imbalanced data set, which is a common problem in machine learning. The proposed method is based on progressive training of a high-resolution VAE model, which can be applied to a wide range of applications, including image impainting, sentence interpolation, and semi-supervised learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper considers the critical problem of routing billions of components in nanoelectronic devices, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
